This is our favorite place to eat when we come visit each year! The food is always great and cooked just right, the fried rice is amazing and worth the extra price for sure! The experience is always great and we’ll continue to come back each year we visit Honolulu! We have a similar style restaurant back home, but this is hands down way better!!! It’s a must try!! :)
I can highly recommend this place. Amazing food and service.

We had the pleasure of dining last night for the first time at Tanaka's East and we were pleasantly surprised by the gracious host, Levin Lou and his staff, From the moment we walked in the door, we felt immersed into a Japanese home & its kitchen. Once seated, the show began... literally, with appetizers and flames coming from the hot plate grill. Aaron, our personal chef, thrilled the table with tricks, bubbling lava volcanos made out of onions and ended with lobster amd filet mignon on a bed of fried rice. We shared our chef with another family, the  Doyle's from Kentucky and they had a dilemma, because they were a family of five and a newborn infant made that a party of six, they weren't expecting that the infant would count as 6, which is not allowed because of Covid. So the staff worked to put three of them on one corner of the huge tables and three at the other side of tables so they were still able to eat together separated by Two Chefs and we had the pleasure of watching little Benjamin's face light up and go a little crazy as the Flames flared in between each course, great Dinner & a Show from Aaron. Great way to spend a Valentine's dinner! We Will definitely go back again.

The atmosphere was wonderful Cody was so entertaining and friendly. The food was cooked to perfection. We are looking forward to dining here again. The table service was prompt and attentive if you are looking for a great meal with some fun, friendly entertainment this is the place to dine.

This is the best location! It is right in Waikiki but just off the main drag. They have easy parking off Kuhio where you can get right in and right out! They will validate for parking as well. The food is phenomenal - never a bad meal. Order the filet, lobster, or shrimp and get a side of salad dressing to dip the seafood in. The restaurant itself is nice because the sliding doors open up and create a nice indoor/outdoor dining feel with good airflow. I don't know why this place isn't packed solid every time I go there. The managers are really on top of it and want to make sure you have the best "experience" rather than just a dinner out. I eat here often and every time the chefs are so good that I don't even have a favorite because they're all amazing. Five stars all around to managers Kevin, Jamie, and Tatianna and last night we had superstar chef Aaron and his sidekick Hong take care of us - water was never empty, plates were never clear of food, and we had an amazing time with almost the whole place to ourselves.
Wonderful experience and we are looking forward to returning.

Thank goodness THEY ARE OPEN! Beautiful setting! Our hibachi chef Aaron put on a great show and the food was delicious! The staff were all so friendly. Can't go wrong with the steak and/ or chicken! White rice was perfect to me. Yet, I assume everything is great. Cocktails were refreshing and tasty as well.  Enjoyed the cucumber cooler.  Would definitely go back!

Came here for date night with friends. For starters,  the place is like the  normal Hibachi type of scene. Cook was nice and did all the tricks well to try to keep us engaged despite our experience. The manager(I think his name was Steve, but I discarded the card)did absolutely nothing but give a half apology, a pen, and his business card. On top of that, our order was messed up. We spend a few hundred and it wasn't worth it at all. Needless to say, our date night was ruined and would would never return or reccomend.

AMAZING!! So as soon as we sat down our drink orders got taken and then someone from management came to welcome us and gave us each a reusable back and some side orders of fried rice, also to wish me a happy birthday. i couldn't believe how personable they were and how much they seemed to care about their customers. then our cook came and he was so good. he was friendly and nice. He had many tricks and treats in his show and the food....OMG i cant even put into words how amazing it was. i ordered the steak and shrimp and my wife ordered the seafood combo and there were a few other ordered of shell fish and we had one person in our party allergic to shell fish and our cook totally accommodated her and made sure to cook her food alone and that made her feel so safe eating there. we never had to wonder where our server was or if we were going to get more drinks, always was there to ask if we needed more refills and anything else. the food was so good and the show amazing that by the time it was time for dessert we realized it was 2 hours later and it didn't even feel like it, we were having so much fun! they then brought out ice cream for everyone and a very cute plate with a cake one it for me and had everyone sing for me....totally funny and embarrassing lol. then they cut it up for the whole party, so yummy too....we got some boxes to take left overs and then before we even got a chance to leave the manager was back again to make sure we had a good time and everything was okay and good. i will totally be back again and be telling everyone about how good of service i had here!
